# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

MCP documentation server powered by [@mcp-framework/docs](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@mcp-framework/docs).

## Setup

1. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

2. Configure your documentation source:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   # Edit .env with your documentation site URL
   ```

3. Build and start:
   ```bash
   npm run build
   npm start
   ```

## MCP Client Configuration

### Claude Code
```bash
claude mcp add {{PROJECT_NAME}} -- node /path/to/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/dist/index.js
```

### Claude Desktop
Add to your `claude_desktop_config.json`:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{PROJECT_NAME}}": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "DOCS_BASE_URL": "https://docs.example.com"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Cursor
Add to your MCP settings:
```json
{
  "{{PROJECT_NAME}}": {
    "command": "node",
    "args": ["/path/to/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/dist/index.js"],
    "env": {
      "DOCS_BASE_URL": "https://docs.example.com"
    }
  }
}
```

## Available Tools

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `search_docs` | Search documentation by keyword or phrase |
| `get_page` | Retrieve full content of a documentation page |
| `list_sections` | Browse the documentation structure |

## Requirements

Your documentation site must serve at least one of:
- `/llms.txt` — documentation index
- `/llms-full.txt` — full documentation content
- `/api/search` — Fumadocs Orama search endpoint (optional, for better search)
